BESHLIN v. McSWEENEY PACKING CO. et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. December 18, 1916.) No. 2876. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Northern District of Texas; Edward R. Meek, Judge. A H. Kirby, of Abilene, Tex., and Theodore Mack, of Ft. Worth, Tex., for appellant. I. W. Stephens and George E. Miller, both of Ft. Worth, Tex., for appellees.

Before PARDEE and WALKER, Circuit Judges, and FOSTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

We find no reversible error in this case, and the decree appealed from is affirmed.
